#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.71"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.71:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.71:0.2"
msgid "7. Migajālavagga"
msgstr "7. With Migajāla"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 71. Paṭhamachaphassāyatanasutta → chaphassāyatanikā 1 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.71:0.3"
msgid "71. Paṭhamachaphassāyatanasutta"
msgstr "71. Six Fields of Contact (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Yo hi koci, bhikkhave, bhikkhu channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ samudayañca "
"atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, anyone who doesn’t truly understand the six fields of contacts’ "
"origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape"

msgctxt "sn35.71:1.2"
msgid "Avusitaṃ tena brahmacariyaṃ, ārakā so imasmā dhammavinayā”ti."
msgstr ""
"has not completed the spiritual journey and is far from this teaching and "
"training.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:2.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, aññataro bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, one of the mendicants said to the Buddha:"

#. VAR: anassasaṃ → anassāsiṃ (bj, pts1) | anassāsaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn35.71:2.2"
msgid "“etthāhaṃ, bhante, anassasaṃ."
msgstr "“Here, sir, I’m lost."

msgctxt "sn35.71:2.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, bhante, channaṃ phassāyatanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca "
"ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For I don’t truly understand the six fields of contacts’ origin, ending, "
"gratification, drawback, and escape.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:3.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, bhikkhu, "
msgstr "“What do you think, mendicant? "

msgctxt "sn35.71:3.2"
msgid "cakkhuṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do you regard the eye like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:4.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

# BB has “you should …” but the text has bhavissati. This is unusual in such a context, and I think it is a specific encouragement for the depressed monk. This would be an example of the Buddha’s knowledge of “where all paths lead”.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhu, bhikkhu, ettha ca te, bhikkhu, cakkhu ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na "
"meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"“Good, mendicant! And regarding the eye, you will truly see clearly with "
"right wisdom that: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn35.71:5.2"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassa … pe …"
msgstr "Just this is the end of suffering."

msgctxt "sn35.71:5.3"
msgid "jivhaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr "Do you regard the ear … nose … tongue … body …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:6.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhu, bhikkhu, ettha ca te, bhikkhu, jivhā ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na "
"meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.71:7.2"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassa … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.71:7.3"
msgid "manaṃ ‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’ti samanupassasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Do you regard the mind like this: ‘This is mine, I am this, this is my "
"self’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:8.1"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.71:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhu, bhikkhu, ettha ca te, bhikkhu, mano ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na "
"meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya sudiṭṭhaṃ bhavissati."
msgstr ""
"“Good, mendicant! And regarding the mind, you will truly see clearly with "
"right wisdom that: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn35.71:9.2"
msgid "Esevanto dukkhassā”ti."
msgstr "Just this is the end of suffering.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.71:9.3"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
